%% Event-Driven Integration Flow - Key domain events across contexts

sequenceDiagram
    participant T as Transaction
    participant CAT as Catalog
    participant INV as Inventory
    participant ACC as Accounting
    participant WQ as Workflow/Queue
    participant PRICE as Pricing

    Note over T: Sale lifecycle
    T->>CAT: Read product (ACL) - name, price, tax
    T->>PRICE: Get effective price / discount
    T->>T: Add line, apply payment
    T->>INV: Publish SaleCompleted (productId, qty)
    T->>ACC: Publish SaleCompleted (amount, journal payload)
    T->>WQ: Publish OrderConfirmed (optional: F&B, Laundry, Bengkel)

    INV->>INV: Deduct stock, emit StockDeducted
    ACC->>ACC: Create journal entries, emit JournalPosted
    WQ->>WQ: Create WorkOrder, emit WorkOrderCreated

    Note over T,WQ: Async event-driven; eventual consistency
